article.headline: Youngstown St. 92, Ill.-Chicago 87
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Quin Humphrey scored 37 points and Youngstown State finished with a 12-6 run to beat Illinois-Chicago 92-87 on Saturday night. It was the Penguins' first win ever over UIC. They also tied a school record by hitting 14 3-pointers in 18 attempts. Humphrey was 13 of 15 from the field including 8 of 9 on 3-pointers. He also had 10 rebounds and seven assists while playing the entire game. Keston Roberts added 21 points, Jack Liles had 15 and Byron Davis 10 points and eight assists for the Penguins (10-13, 5-7 Horizon League). Jovan Stefanov scored 19 points, Othyus Jeffers 18, Josh Mayo 16, T.J. Gray 13 and Scott Vandermeer 10 for the Flames (9-15, 4-7). Stefanov's tip-in with 3:04 left gave UIC an 81-80 lead, but Roberts started the Penguins' late surge with a tip-in that gave them the lead for good. Roberts then hit a 3-pointer. Davis and John Barber each hit two free throws in the final minute to help Youngstown State hang on.
